sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M12071
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: hin invertase under constitutive promoter pspv from Salmonella
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part codes for the protein hin, which acts a flippase. The promoter under this device is constitutive.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Logan Trimble
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This device comes from multiple BioBrick parts.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We needed the flippase to act with a constitutive promoter in order to serve the function for the coin flipper device in our system.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K112707
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
The spv promoter. ---- This part is in BBb Format. It is flanked by BamHI and BglII sites instead of XbaI and SpeI. More information about the BBb Format is available at:
[http://openwetware.org/wiki/Template:AndersonLab:BBb_Standard BBb Standard Description Page]

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Hin
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Generates the Salmonella typhimurium Hin protein. This protein is used to invert DNA that is flanked by Hix siteds.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Erin Zwack, Sabriya Rosemond

sbol:SequenceAnnotation.dcterms:title: Mutation to delete the SpeI site
